 An Audi Q7 was about to turn towards the Middelburg Airfield when a Hyundai Elantra struck the Audi from behind. The BMW sedan was amongst the three vehicles that collided on Saturday morning. Frustrated family members had an altercation with a firefighter when they were told not to take pictures of the man, who was driving the Hyundai Elantra, inside an ambulance. Two people were rushed to hospital for treatment. • In an unrelated incident, three vehicles were also involved in an accident on Saturday morning.
The incident occurred on the corner of Walter Sisulu and Protea Street. Just Coal Mine employees who were travelling in the Iveco had to return home. The collision involved an Iveco which was travelling to Just Coal Mine, a Corsa bakkie and a BMW sedan. The driver of the Corsa bakkie was amongst the six people who were transported to the hospital. Passengers of the Iveco told www.mobserver.co.za that the traffic lights were not operating, however, they are unclear as to how the three vehicles collided. Six people sustained injuries, they were transported to the hospital for treatment. The driver of the Hydundai Elantra was rushed to hospital.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za